C LBd
(* Weakestmo (Chakraborty & Vafeiadis, POPL 2019), LB+data ("LBd"): a REAL data  *)
(* dependency on BOTH threads — each store's value is a function (r+1) of the      *)
(* value just loaded, so dependsReally classifies both data edges isSemantic=true. *)
(* The r0=r1=1 outcome would be a value justified only by itself around the        *)
(* dep u rf cycle — an out-of-thin-air read. Weakestmo FORBIDS it: the semantic    *)
(* data dependencies land in sdep and jfCoherence sees a cycle in sdep u jf.       *)
{ }
 P0                        | P1                        ;
 r0 = READ_ONCE(*x)        | r1 = READ_ONCE(*y)        ;
 WRITE_ONCE(*y, r0 + 1)    | WRITE_ONCE(*x, r1 + 1)    ;
exists (0:r0=1 /\ 1:r1=1)
